dublin_core.dcvalue: Missed diagnosis of acute myocardial infarction is associated with adverse clinical outcomes and more dollars recovered in malpractice suits than any other condition The rate of missed diagnosis varies between emergency departments EDs we hypothesized that it is associated with the volume of acute myocardial infarction patients treated in an ED and that the association can be explained by other hospital characteristics
The risk of missed diagnosis of acute myocardial infarction associated with emergency department volume.
